	body {
		background-color: #eee;
	}
	.contents {
		background: white;
		font-family: Georgia, serif;
		font-size: 13px;
		border: 1px #888 solid;
		padding: 0 1em;
	}
	code {
		font-size: 90%;
	}
	</style>'

beginTag div 'contents'

Markdown.pl <<"EOF"|SmartyPants.pl
# TODO Bundle Help

The "Show TODO List" command will scan your current document (on disk) or documents in your project for lines containing certain tags (see below).
It will show an ordered list of these tags and their context which can be clicked to jump to that line in that file.

## Tags

Preconfigured tags are:

- <span style="color: #A00000;">FIXME</span>
- <span style="color: #CF830D;">TODO</span>
- <span style="color: #008000;">CHANGED</span>
- <span style="color: #0090C8;">RADAR</span>

Those tags consist of a label (like "TODO"), a color in which they will be printed and a regular expression to transform them. They can be adapted in the "Show TODO List" command (which is written in ruby 1.8 -- it will not work on Panther, sorry) by changing or adding to the `$tags` variable. Rearranging the entries will rearrange them in the output, too.

## Hints

The list is not directly printable, but you can _Select All_ and use the _TextEdit_ Service ("New Window containing Selection") from the _Services_ Menu (in the _TextMate_ menu)
EOF

endTag
htmlFooter
